El-Erian Says S&P Negative Outlook One of ‘Unthinkable Things' to Happen

-- B y   D e n n i s   F i t z g e r a l d
-- 
2011-04-19T13:59:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-19/el-erian-says-s-p-negative-outlook-one-of-unthinkable-things-to-happen.html
The  Standard & Poor’s  change
yesterday in its outlook for the U.S. AAA credit rating to
negative is one of the “unthinkable” things that have
happened, said Mohamed El-Erian, chief executive officer at
Pacific Investment Management Co., in a radio interview on
“Bloomberg Surveillance” with  Tom Keene .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dennis Fitzgerald at 
 dfitzgerald5@bloomberg.net  